WEBVTT

1
00:01:25.254 --> 00:01:26.713
[WIND HOWLING]

2
00:01:29.216 --> 00:01:31.218
NARRATOR:
<i>My life fades</i>…

3
00:01:32.094 --> 00:01:33.720
…<i>the vision dims.</i>

4
00:01:34.638 --> 00:01:37.391
<i>All that remains are memories.</i>

5
00:01:38.600 --> 00:01:42.437
<i>I remember a time of chaos</i>…

6
00:01:43.230 --> 00:01:46.900
…<i>ruined dreams, this wasted land.</i>

7
00:01:47.943 --> 00:01:52.114
<i>But most of all,
I remember the Road Warrior</i>…

8
00:01:52.948 --> 00:01:55.158
…<i>the man we called Max.</i>

9
00:01:56.201 --> 00:01:59.997
<i>To understand who he was,
you have to go back to another time</i>…

10
00:02:00.831 --> 00:02:03.834
…<i>when the world was powered
by the black fuel</i>…

11
00:02:04.376 --> 00:02:08.630
…<i>and the deserts sprouted
great cities of pipe and steel.</i>

12
00:02:11.174 --> 00:02:13.802
<i>Gone now, swept away.</i>

13
00:02:14.553 --> 00:02:18.932
<i>For reasons long forgotten,
two mighty warrior tribes went to war</i>…

14
00:02:19.349 --> 00:02:22.602
…<i>and touched off a blaze
which engulfed them all.</i>

15
00:02:23.270 --> 00:02:27.274
<i>Without fuel they were nothing.
They'd built a house of straw.</i>

16
00:02:27.983 --> 00:02:31.320
<i>The thundering machines
sputtered and stopped.</i>

17
00:02:34.197 --> 00:02:38.702
<i>Their leaders talked
and talked and talked.</i>

18
00:02:41.913 --> 00:02:44.541
<i>But nothing could stem the avalanche.</i>

19
00:02:45.792 --> 00:02:47.627
<i>Their world crumbled</i>…

20
00:02:48.587 --> 00:02:50.630
…<i>the cities exploded.</i>

21
00:02:51.465 --> 00:02:53.342
<i>A whirlwind of looting</i>…

22
00:02:54.259 --> 00:02:56.553
…<i>a firestorm of fear.</i>

23
00:02:57.554 --> 00:03:00.057
<i>Men began to feed on men.</i>

24
00:03:02.059 --> 00:03:05.103
<i>On the roads,
it was a white-line nightmare.</i>

25
00:03:05.812 --> 00:03:08.482
<i>Only those mobile enough to scavenge</i>…

26
00:03:09.024 --> 00:03:11.777
…<i>brutal enough to pillage,
would survive.</i>

27
00:03:12.736 --> 00:03:15.155
<i>The gangs took over the highways</i>…

28
00:03:15.822 --> 00:03:19.201
…<i>ready to wage war for a tank of juice.</i>

29
00:03:20.744 --> 00:03:23.288
<i>And in this maelstrom of decay</i>…

30
00:03:23.789 --> 00:03:26.625
…<i>ordinary men
were battered and smashed.</i>

31
00:03:27.459 --> 00:03:28.960
<i>Men like Max.</i>

32
00:03:29.711 --> 00:03:31.380
<i>The warrior Max.</i>

33
00:03:34.424 --> 00:03:37.511
<i>In the roar of an engine,
he lost everything</i>…

34
00:03:43.058 --> 00:03:45.185
…<i>and became a shell of a man.</i>

35
00:03:45.602 --> 00:03:48.105
<i>A burnt-out, desolate man.</i>

36
00:03:48.897 --> 00:03:52.984
<i>A man haunted by
the demons of his past.</i>

37
00:03:53.985 --> 00:03:57.531
<i>A man who wandered out
into the wasteland.</i>

38
00:03:59.366 --> 00:04:00.909
<i>And it was here</i>…

39
00:04:02.285 --> 00:04:04.162
…<i>in this blighted place</i>…

40
00:04:06.039 --> 00:04:08.291
…<i>that he learned to live again.</i>

41
00:04:44.244 --> 00:04:46.204
[TIRES SCREECHING]

42
00:04:56.339 --> 00:04:57.591
[BEEPING]

43
00:05:09.352 --> 00:05:11.354
[WHIMPERING]

44
00:05:27.412 --> 00:05:28.622
[TIRES SCREECHING]

45
00:06:51.705 --> 00:06:53.790
[WEZ SCREAMING]

46
00:08:07.656 --> 00:08:09.991
[MAN SHRIEKING]

47
00:08:31.846 --> 00:08:34.849
["HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU" CHIMES]

48
00:09:04.170 --> 00:09:06.172
[WIND HOWLING]

49
00:10:18.620 --> 00:10:20.622
[SNAKE HISSING]

50
00:10:28.379 --> 00:10:29.923
[HISSES]

51
00:10:32.759 --> 00:10:34.427
[GYRO CAPTAIN SCREAMS]

52
00:10:35.929 --> 00:10:38.765
Don't hurt the snake. Put it down.

53
00:10:39.224 --> 00:10:42.435
Gently, gently. Nice. Nice.

54
00:10:42.602 --> 00:10:44.103
Now the iron.

55
00:10:47.315 --> 00:10:48.566
The gun.

56
00:10:49.818 --> 00:10:52.821
Down, down. Turn around.

57
00:10:53.738 --> 00:10:56.241
[GYRO CAPTAIN CACKLES]

58
00:10:57.575 --> 00:10:59.452
[WHOOPING AND GRUNTING]

59
00:11:05.542 --> 00:11:08.002
Looks like I got myself some
gasoline, eh?

60
00:11:08.169 --> 00:11:11.005
Eh? V8? Huh?

61
00:11:11.172 --> 00:11:13.842
Booby-trapped.
Touch those tanks and:

62
00:11:14.008 --> 00:11:15.677
[IMITATES EXPLOSION]

63
00:11:22.976 --> 00:11:25.687
Booby trap. Back up.

64
00:11:27.021 --> 00:11:30.400
Oh, you crafty little man, you.

65
00:11:30.567 --> 00:11:33.403
You're quick, very quick.

66
00:11:34.696 --> 00:11:38.658
Never seen a man beat the snake before.
Who are you?

67
00:11:40.869 --> 00:11:44.163
Reflexes. Yeah. That's what you've got.

68
00:11:46.165 --> 00:11:48.334
Me, I got brains.

69
00:11:52.630 --> 00:11:53.631
Hey!

70
00:11:55.508 --> 00:11:58.303
A fella, a quick fella…

71
00:11:58.761 --> 00:12:03.141
… might have a weapon under there.
I'd have to pin his head to the panel.

72
00:12:15.194 --> 00:12:17.697
Hey. Hey, hey.

73
00:12:20.658 --> 00:12:22.577
Don't play me the fool.

74
00:12:24.829 --> 00:12:26.497
[DOG BARKS]
[GYRO CAPTAIN YELLS]

75
00:12:29.375 --> 00:12:32.921
Gas, fuel, gasoline!
Thousands of gallons of it!

76
00:12:33.087 --> 00:12:35.256
- As much as you want!
- Where? Where?

77
00:12:35.423 --> 00:12:37.967
Twenty miles from here.
Pumping it, they are. Refining!

78
00:12:38.134 --> 00:12:39.719
[IMITATES FUEL PUMPING]

79
00:12:40.178 --> 00:12:42.138
- A huge tanker full.
- Crap.

80
00:12:42.305 --> 00:12:44.724
No. No, no, no, it's true! It's true.

81
00:12:45.016 --> 00:12:47.977
It's not self-service, no, no.
It's too hard for me.

82
00:12:48.144 --> 00:12:51.064
- But a man of your ingenuity…
- Where? Where? Where?

83
00:12:52.148 --> 00:12:54.567
Kill me and you'll never find out.

84
00:12:57.820 --> 00:12:58.905
All right. Come on.

85
00:12:59.405 --> 00:13:01.407
[DOG BARKING]

86
00:13:10.750 --> 00:13:13.169
[GYRO CAPTAIN CHUCKLING]

87
00:13:14.963 --> 00:13:17.548
Good dog. Nice doggy, eh?

88
00:13:18.633 --> 00:13:20.009
Good doggy.

89
00:13:22.595 --> 00:13:24.097
[GYRO CAPTAIN GASPS]

90
00:13:26.724 --> 00:13:27.934
Bless you, dog.

91
00:13:48.621 --> 00:13:51.290
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER SPEAKER]

92
00:13:51.958 --> 00:13:55.003
Well, there it is.

93
00:13:55.169 --> 00:13:57.797
[PEOPLE SHOUTING IN DISTANCE]

94
00:13:57.964 --> 00:13:59.966
GYRO CAPTAIN:
Four days I was up here…

95
00:14:00.466 --> 00:14:04.470
… me and the snakes,
playing mahjong, taking tea…

96
00:14:05.555 --> 00:14:07.432
… watching, thinking…

97
00:14:08.307 --> 00:14:11.144
… how was I gonna
get in and get the gas?

98
00:14:13.271 --> 00:14:15.398
Day and night it's pumping.

99
00:14:15.565 --> 00:14:17.900
[GYRO CAPTAIN
IMITATES FUEL PUMPING]

100
00:14:18.651 --> 00:14:20.153
Fuel to burn.

101
00:14:21.279 --> 00:14:24.866
They've got the lot.
Power, lights, you name it.

102
00:14:25.992 --> 00:14:28.619
You can bet your life
they mean to keep it.

103
00:14:29.495 --> 00:14:31.289
Thirty of them in there.

104
00:14:31.497 --> 00:14:33.958
Arrows, flamethrowers, guns.

105
00:14:35.334 --> 00:14:38.046
No place for man or reptile, I thought.

106
00:14:39.213 --> 00:14:41.340
Then this trash arrived…

107
00:14:42.425 --> 00:14:44.177
… as moths to a flame.

108
00:14:44.594 --> 00:14:47.388
Round and round, attack, attack…

109
00:14:48.264 --> 00:14:52.101
… like angry ants,
mad with the smell of gasoline.

110
00:14:53.978 --> 00:14:55.980
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

111
00:15:08.034 --> 00:15:11.162
GYRO CAPTAIN:
In the tanker, that's where they keep it.

112
00:15:12.371 --> 00:15:15.208
Thousands of gallons.
As much as you want.

113
00:15:17.710 --> 00:15:20.546
If anyone's gonna get in there,
it's gonna be you.

114
00:15:20.880 --> 00:15:24.175
Me, I'm gonna feed the snakes.

115
00:15:28.137 --> 00:15:31.808
A man lives by his word, I reckon,
and I've kept mine, eh?

116
00:15:37.438 --> 00:15:38.981
[GROANS]

117
00:15:41.234 --> 00:15:44.195
Look, we had a deal. I show you the gas
and you let me go, right?

118
00:15:44.362 --> 00:15:48.324
- The arrangement was I wouldn't kill you.
- After all I've done for you…

119
00:15:48.825 --> 00:15:51.452
I reckon you got a bargain, don't you?

120
00:16:19.814 --> 00:16:22.233
HUMUNGUS [OVER SPEAKER]:
<i>Attack, my vermin, attack!</i>

121
00:16:46.716 --> 00:16:50.636
<i>Onward! Bring me the fuel.
For the glory of Humungus.</i>

122
00:16:50.928 --> 00:16:53.264
<i>For the great glory of Humungus.</i>

123
00:16:57.977 --> 00:17:00.104
<i>Smegma crazies to the left!</i>

124
00:17:03.065 --> 00:17:05.818
<i>The gate! Gayboy berserkers to the gate!</i>

125
00:17:12.950 --> 00:17:14.493
<i>I am your Lord.</i>

126
00:17:19.498 --> 00:17:20.708
<i>Attack!</i>

127
00:17:42.813 --> 00:17:45.399
[SNARLING AND BARKING]

128
00:18:03.209 --> 00:18:05.878
[SIREN WAILING]

129
00:18:13.010 --> 00:18:15.721
[TRUMPET BLARING]

130
00:19:07.648 --> 00:19:09.650
[WIND HOWLING]

131
00:19:35.176 --> 00:19:37.803
[SIREN WAILING]

132
00:19:37.970 --> 00:19:40.348
[PEOPLE SHOUTING]

133
00:19:43.601 --> 00:19:47.271
[HUMUNGUS SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER SPEAKER]

134
00:20:53.712 --> 00:20:55.381
[WEAPONS FIRING]

135
00:21:23.742 --> 00:21:26.245
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

136
00:21:47.516 --> 00:21:48.934
[SCREAMS]

137
00:23:04.343 --> 00:23:06.345
[ENGINE REVVING]

138
00:23:38.711 --> 00:23:40.713
[MAN WHISTLING]

139
00:24:07.740 --> 00:24:10.743
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

140
00:24:10.909 --> 00:24:12.119
Save it.

141
00:24:12.578 --> 00:24:14.830
I'm just here for the gasoline.

142
00:24:14.997 --> 00:24:16.290
Yeah. Yeah.

143
00:24:22.087 --> 00:24:23.881
As much as you like.

144
00:24:24.048 --> 00:24:26.008
Just take me back there.

145
00:24:48.614 --> 00:24:50.032
[NATHAN GRUNTS]

146
00:24:58.123 --> 00:25:00.125
[WIND HOWLING]

147
00:25:12.930 --> 00:25:15.474
PAPPAGALLO:
Show your weapons and come forward!

148
00:25:19.812 --> 00:25:21.188
Steady now.

149
00:25:23.232 --> 00:25:25.192
Take it real easy.

150
00:25:26.443 --> 00:25:28.362
That's as far as you go.

151
00:25:29.071 --> 00:25:30.489
Turn around.

152
00:25:31.490 --> 00:25:33.409
BIG REBECCA:
Nathan! Nathan! It's Nathan!

153
00:25:33.575 --> 00:25:34.868
ZETTA:
Hurry, get the stretcher!

154
00:25:35.035 --> 00:25:36.286
PAPPAGALLO:
Lose them.

155
00:25:39.540 --> 00:25:41.041
ZETTA:
Open the gate.

156
00:25:46.213 --> 00:25:48.590
Hurry up with that damned stretcher.

157
00:25:49.007 --> 00:25:50.050
BIG REBECCA:
Nathan!

158
00:25:50.217 --> 00:25:53.178
Hey, that's fine. It's fine. Just stay here.

159
00:25:53.679 --> 00:25:55.472
Cover him. Cover him.

160
00:25:55.681 --> 00:25:57.683
[BIG REBECCA CRYING]

161
00:25:57.850 --> 00:25:59.727
Come on, quick. Quick.

162
00:26:00.602 --> 00:26:02.312
BIG REBECCA:
Oh, what a waste!

163
00:26:03.355 --> 00:26:05.023
MAN:
Watch his leg.

164
00:26:08.026 --> 00:26:10.070
BIG REBECCA:
You and your handiwork!

165
00:26:10.237 --> 00:26:12.030
He didn't stand a chance!

166
00:26:12.197 --> 00:26:15.909
Oh, I warned him. You all heard me.
"Madness," I said.

167
00:26:16.160 --> 00:26:19.538
"We can escape, take our gas," he said.
"How?" I said.

168
00:26:19.705 --> 00:26:21.832
ZETTA: Get that machine inside.
Charlie, help me—

169
00:26:21.999 --> 00:26:23.208
Derek?

170
00:26:29.882 --> 00:26:31.550
ZETTA:
Get that machine inside.

171
00:26:32.217 --> 00:26:33.802
Close the damned gate.

172
00:26:33.969 --> 00:26:36.221
MAN: Mind your backs,
mind your backs. Coming through.

173
00:26:48.567 --> 00:26:50.944
ZETTA:
All right, give him room, give him room.

174
00:26:54.490 --> 00:26:55.908
Who are you?

175
00:26:56.950 --> 00:26:59.077
How did you get through out there?

176
00:26:59.244 --> 00:27:02.164
Look, I want some answers.
Where did you find him?

177
00:27:02.581 --> 00:27:05.918
Two or three miles down the road,
left for dead. We had a deal.

178
00:27:06.084 --> 00:27:08.378
There were three other vehicles.
Did you see them?

179
00:27:08.545 --> 00:27:10.923
They're heading to the southwest
in heaps of trouble.

180
00:27:11.089 --> 00:27:13.592
He said if I brought him back,
you'd give me some gas.

181
00:27:13.759 --> 00:27:16.929
- Now, there's not much time.
- There was a woman in the car.

182
00:27:18.013 --> 00:27:19.389
She's dead.

183
00:27:21.099 --> 00:27:22.309
What did they do?

184
00:27:22.476 --> 00:27:25.270
It was quick. I just want my gas,
I wanna get out of here.

185
00:27:25.437 --> 00:27:27.815
For all we know, he's one of them.
Give him nothing.

186
00:27:27.981 --> 00:27:29.650
CURMUDGEON:
She's right, he's a parasite.

187
00:27:29.817 --> 00:27:32.694
Trading in human flesh. Mercenary trash.

188
00:27:33.862 --> 00:27:36.865
- We had an arrangement.
- What do you mean, an arrangement?

189
00:27:37.032 --> 00:27:38.784
You talk to this man.

190
00:27:39.576 --> 00:27:42.996
BIG REBECCA:
No, no. Try something. Try something.

191
00:27:44.289 --> 00:27:46.333
[SOBBING]

192
00:27:56.385 --> 00:27:59.096
If you had a contract, it was with him.

193
00:27:59.263 --> 00:28:00.973
And it died with him.

194
00:28:01.139 --> 00:28:03.141
- Get rid of him.
- Move it.

195
00:28:03.475 --> 00:28:04.643
MECHANIC:
Left!

196
00:28:07.271 --> 00:28:08.480
Left.

197
00:28:12.276 --> 00:28:15.571
Gotta hand it to you, treasure.
The last of the V8 Interceptors.

198
00:28:15.737 --> 00:28:17.447
A piece of history.

199
00:28:19.074 --> 00:28:21.368
Would have been a shame to blow it up.

200
00:28:22.995 --> 00:28:24.746
[GROWLING AND BARKING]

201
00:28:30.794 --> 00:28:32.296
Let him go!

202
00:28:34.965 --> 00:28:35.966
It's all right, mate.

203
00:28:36.133 --> 00:28:39.761
LOOKOUT: Here they come!
Close the gates! They're coming back!

204
00:29:47.829 --> 00:29:49.164
[SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY]

205
00:29:49.331 --> 00:29:53.460
Hold your fire! He comes in peace!

206
00:29:53.835 --> 00:29:58.256
- For Christ's sake, hold your fire!
- Shut up.

207
00:30:00.384 --> 00:30:02.886
[BROKEN VICTIM
SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

208
00:30:39.965 --> 00:30:41.842
[ENGINES STOP]

209
00:30:51.143 --> 00:30:53.478
TOADIE:
Greetings from the Humungus!

210
00:30:54.146 --> 00:30:55.814
The Lord Humungus!

211
00:30:56.565 --> 00:30:59.317
The Warrior of the Wasteland!

212
00:31:01.445 --> 00:31:05.157
The Ayatollah of Rock 'n' Roll-ah!

213
00:31:07.826 --> 00:31:10.078
HUMUNGUS:
I am gravely disappointed.

214
00:31:10.662 --> 00:31:13.832
Again you have made me
unleash my dogs of war.

215
00:31:14.499 --> 00:31:16.334
- Look at what remains…
- Help!

216
00:31:16.501 --> 00:31:18.503
- … of your gallant scouts.
- Kill him now…

217
00:31:18.670 --> 00:31:21.965
- Why? Because you're selfish.
- … while you've got the chance.

218
00:31:22.132 --> 00:31:23.842
You hoard your gasoline.

219
00:31:24.509 --> 00:31:27.262
- You will not listen to reason.
- Don't listen to him!

220
00:31:27.429 --> 00:31:29.514
HUMUNGUS:
Now, my prisoners say…

221
00:31:29.765 --> 00:31:33.101
… you plan to take your gasoline
out of the wasteland.

222
00:31:33.518 --> 00:31:36.897
You sent them out this morning
to find a vehicle.

223
00:31:37.439 --> 00:31:41.735
A rig big enough to haul
that fat tank of gas.

224
00:31:42.527 --> 00:31:44.196
What a puny plan.

225
00:31:44.821 --> 00:31:46.406
Look around you.

226
00:31:48.617 --> 00:31:50.994
This is the Valley of Death.

227
00:31:51.161 --> 00:31:52.204
See!

228
00:31:52.954 --> 00:31:56.875
Nothing can escape!
The Humungus rules the wasteland!

229
00:31:57.042 --> 00:32:01.213
Give them nothing. Blow it up.
Give them—

230
00:32:01.463 --> 00:32:02.714
[MEN LAUGHING]

231
00:32:03.006 --> 00:32:05.050
HUMUNGUS:
Humungus will not be defied.

232
00:32:05.217 --> 00:32:06.760
[GRUNTS]

233
00:32:15.560 --> 00:32:16.561
[GRUNTS]

234
00:32:27.614 --> 00:32:29.366
HUMUNGUS:
Wez. Wez.

235
00:32:29.908 --> 00:32:31.701
- Listen to me!
- Aah!

236
00:32:38.291 --> 00:32:40.085
I got it. I got it.

237
00:32:40.252 --> 00:32:41.878
[MEN CHATTERING]

238
00:32:42.754 --> 00:32:44.756
[MEN LAUGHING]

239
00:32:45.507 --> 00:32:46.842
[GRUNTS]

240
00:32:48.301 --> 00:32:49.302
MAN:
Good one.

241
00:32:54.558 --> 00:32:57.727
HUMUNGUS:
Quiet. Quiet. No more games.

242
00:32:58.812 --> 00:33:00.355
No more games!

243
00:33:01.064 --> 00:33:02.899
We are here for a purpose.

244
00:33:03.441 --> 00:33:05.277
We've come with an offer.

245
00:33:07.404 --> 00:33:08.613
[GROWLS]

246
00:33:08.780 --> 00:33:12.117
No. No more talk.

247
00:33:12.325 --> 00:33:14.619
We go in. We kill.

248
00:33:14.786 --> 00:33:16.913
We'll kill them!

249
00:33:19.624 --> 00:33:23.044
We'll kill them! Kill them. Kill them!

250
00:33:25.297 --> 00:33:26.965
HUMUNGUS:
Do you see him?

251
00:33:30.135 --> 00:33:32.137
Kill! Kill!

252
00:33:32.387 --> 00:33:34.973
[GRUNTING]

253
00:33:35.182 --> 00:33:37.100
HUMUNGUS:
Be still, my dog of war.

254
00:33:37.350 --> 00:33:39.269
I understand your pain.

255
00:33:39.561 --> 00:33:43.481
We all lost someone we love.
But we do it my way.

256
00:33:43.648 --> 00:33:45.609
Losers. Losers wait.

257
00:33:45.817 --> 00:33:47.819
HUMUNGUS:
We do it my way.

258
00:33:47.986 --> 00:33:52.616
Their fear is our ally.
The gasoline will be ours.

259
00:33:53.366 --> 00:33:55.952
Then you shall have your revenge.

260
00:34:01.333 --> 00:34:02.709
Take him away.

261
00:34:06.129 --> 00:34:08.798
[WEZ GASPING]

262
00:34:17.557 --> 00:34:21.436
HUMUNGUS: There has been
too much violence, too much pain.

263
00:34:22.187 --> 00:34:24.189
None here are without sin.

264
00:34:25.607 --> 00:34:27.692
But I have an honorable compromise.

265
00:34:28.693 --> 00:34:30.237
Just walk away.

266
00:34:30.862 --> 00:34:32.530
Give me the pump…

267
00:34:32.906 --> 00:34:34.199
… the oil…

268
00:34:34.824 --> 00:34:36.326
… the gasoline…

269
00:34:36.785 --> 00:34:40.330
… and the whole compound,
and I'll spare your lives.

270
00:34:41.039 --> 00:34:45.460
Just walk away. I will give you
safe passage in the wasteland.

271
00:34:46.044 --> 00:34:49.714
Just walk away
and there will be an end to the horror.

272
00:34:50.548 --> 00:34:52.259
[ENGINE STARTS]

273
00:34:55.220 --> 00:34:56.972
I await your answer.

274
00:34:57.430 --> 00:34:59.766
You have one full day to decide.

275
00:35:27.252 --> 00:35:29.087
We'll never walk away!

276
00:35:30.422 --> 00:35:31.589
Never!

277
00:35:53.236 --> 00:35:56.323
You heard what he said.
It sounds reasonable.

278
00:35:56.906 --> 00:35:59.117
We don't have to die.

279
00:35:59.617 --> 00:36:01.828
All we have to do is walk away.

280
00:36:01.995 --> 00:36:03.330
WARRIOR WOMAN:
No. We've worked too hard.

281
00:36:03.496 --> 00:36:05.749
BIG REBECCA: It's simple.
All we do is change the fuel…

282
00:36:05.915 --> 00:36:07.584
… and this junkyard for our lives.

283
00:36:07.751 --> 00:36:10.128
Look, if we walk out there,
they'll slaughter us.

284
00:36:10.295 --> 00:36:13.506
They'll set us loose
and then cut us down like pigs.

285
00:36:13.673 --> 00:36:15.050
Don't listen to them.

286
00:36:15.216 --> 00:36:17.635
All right. All right. This is it.

287
00:36:18.011 --> 00:36:20.138
I'll talk to this Humungus.

288
00:36:20.638 --> 00:36:21.639
MAN:
Bloody fool.

289
00:36:21.806 --> 00:36:23.683
He's a reasonable man…

290
00:36:24.684 --> 00:36:26.644
… open to negotiation.

291
00:36:27.103 --> 00:36:30.106
He promised us safe passage.
He gave his word.

292
00:36:30.273 --> 00:36:32.525
PAPPAGALLO:
And let us suppose he keeps it…

293
00:36:33.151 --> 00:36:36.738
… and we walk away from here
with our lives. What then?

294
00:36:40.325 --> 00:36:42.827
[PEOPLE SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY NEARBY]

295
00:37:13.191 --> 00:37:15.860
["HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU" CHIMES]

296
00:37:40.635 --> 00:37:42.637
[GRUNTING]

297
00:37:46.015 --> 00:37:47.517
But remember.

298
00:37:47.684 --> 00:37:51.312
Remember one thing.
That is more than just a tanker of gas.

299
00:37:51.479 --> 00:37:55.900
That is our lifeline to a place
beyond that vermin on machines.

300
00:37:56.568 --> 00:37:58.862
That's 2000 miles from here!

301
00:37:59.529 --> 00:38:02.615
How do you expect us to get it there?
Drag it?

302
00:38:02.782 --> 00:38:05.577
If we have to, yes.
There's always a way.

303
00:38:06.578 --> 00:38:08.288
But the first step…

304
00:38:09.330 --> 00:38:10.915
… defend the fuel.

305
00:38:12.167 --> 00:38:13.334
Words.

306
00:38:14.085 --> 00:38:15.462
Just words!

307
00:38:16.129 --> 00:38:17.755
You'd die for a pipe dream!

308
00:38:17.922 --> 00:38:20.758
Wrong. We fight for a belief. I stay.

309
00:38:29.893 --> 00:38:32.270
CAPTAIN'S GIRL:
I wish it could have worked, Pappagallo.

310
00:38:32.437 --> 00:38:34.689
You can't expect to compete with that.

311
00:38:35.273 --> 00:38:38.818
Every day we get weaker
while they get stronger. It's finished.

312
00:38:39.444 --> 00:38:40.778
I'm sorry.

313
00:38:43.781 --> 00:38:45.116
[WHISTLES]

314
00:38:47.118 --> 00:38:50.663
Two days ago I saw a vehicle
that'd haul that tanker.

315
00:38:52.332 --> 00:38:54.542
You wanna get out of here…

316
00:38:55.168 --> 00:38:56.711
… you talk to me.

317
00:39:01.966 --> 00:39:03.968
MAX:
Okay, so that's my offer.

318
00:39:04.302 --> 00:39:06.554
I deliver a rig big enough
to haul that tanker…

319
00:39:06.721 --> 00:39:10.141
… you give me back my vehicle
and as much juice as I can carry.

320
00:39:10.308 --> 00:39:12.477
We lost eight good people this morning.

321
00:39:14.979 --> 00:39:16.856
What's he got in mind?

322
00:39:17.398 --> 00:39:20.401
Now, to do the job
I need five gallons of diesel…

323
00:39:20.652 --> 00:39:22.570
… and some high-octane gasoline.

324
00:39:26.282 --> 00:39:28.201
Think of it as a down payment.

325
00:39:28.493 --> 00:39:30.995
And that's the last we'll ever see of him.

326
00:39:31.162 --> 00:39:33.331
He has to come back for his wheels.

327
00:39:33.748 --> 00:39:35.542
What have we got to lose?

328
00:39:37.835 --> 00:39:39.671
You've got yourself a deal.

329
00:40:04.320 --> 00:40:07.156
My vehicle and all the juice I can carry.

330
00:40:21.212 --> 00:40:23.715
[WOLF HOWLS IN DISTANCE]

331
00:40:35.893 --> 00:40:38.896
[PEOPLE LAUGHING AND SHOUTING
IN DISTANCE]

332
00:40:58.249 --> 00:40:59.709
[WHISPERS]
Come on, dog.

333
00:41:01.044 --> 00:41:02.420
Shh!

334
00:41:21.356 --> 00:41:23.191
[HOWLING NEARBY]

335
00:41:23.941 --> 00:41:26.235
[IMITATES DOG HOWLING]

336
00:43:10.673 --> 00:43:12.675
[WIND HOWLING]

337
00:43:33.404 --> 00:43:35.198
[DOG BARKING]

338
00:43:53.758 --> 00:43:56.928
GYRO CAPTAIN: You know what
I miss most of all? Clean women.

339
00:43:57.970 --> 00:44:00.681
Nail polish, perfume…

340
00:44:01.432 --> 00:44:05.269
… the smell of bicycle seats, cocktails…

341
00:44:05.937 --> 00:44:07.605
MAX: Shut up.
GYRO CAPTAIN: Desserts.

342
00:44:08.481 --> 00:44:12.276
Lingerie. Remember lingerie?

343
00:44:20.785 --> 00:44:22.912
[GYRO CAPTAIN LAUGHS]

344
00:44:23.079 --> 00:44:25.456
I knew it. I knew it'd work.

345
00:44:25.748 --> 00:44:29.669
Lethal. Lethal, these snakes. Born killers.

346
00:44:31.462 --> 00:44:32.463
Down!

347
00:44:32.630 --> 00:44:35.675
It's my snake. I trained it.
I'm gonna eat it.

348
00:44:36.092 --> 00:44:39.220
So find your own. Get out of it.

349
00:44:39.887 --> 00:44:42.807
I've got a recipe for snake. Delicious.

350
00:44:43.641 --> 00:44:46.269
Fricassee of reptile. Get out.

351
00:44:46.686 --> 00:44:48.938
Better than your dog food. No!

352
00:44:49.647 --> 00:44:53.025
Pure protein, minerals, vitamins.

353
00:44:53.526 --> 00:44:55.987
A man's gotta look after himself.

354
00:44:56.279 --> 00:44:58.656
Healthy mind, healthy body, dog.

355
00:44:58.865 --> 00:45:02.577
Hey! You are what you eat, I reckon.
Get away!

356
00:45:03.661 --> 00:45:06.497
You two ought to take a look
in the mirror some time.

357
00:45:06.664 --> 00:45:08.708
No style, no taste.

358
00:45:10.835 --> 00:45:12.003
Empty.

359
00:45:12.837 --> 00:45:14.672
All this time.

360
00:45:18.843 --> 00:45:21.804
That's dishonest. Low.

361
00:45:25.099 --> 00:45:27.643
Let's have a look
at this machine of yours.

362
00:45:28.519 --> 00:45:30.855
How do I know that one's not a dud?

363
00:45:31.647 --> 00:45:34.609
- Find out.
- Cool. Cool, cool.

364
00:45:35.693 --> 00:45:39.363
Now, you've gotta understand the basics
of aerodynamics in a thing like this.

365
00:45:39.530 --> 00:45:40.865
MAX:
Shut up. Shut up.

366
00:46:02.261 --> 00:46:04.597
[ENGINE STALLING]

367
00:46:14.649 --> 00:46:16.317
[ENGINE STARTS]

368
00:46:19.695 --> 00:46:22.365
[GYRO CAPTAIN WHOOPING]

369
00:46:22.907 --> 00:46:25.826
Hey! Hey, hey, hey.

370
00:46:26.243 --> 00:46:29.455
What about me, eh?
You're not gonna leave me here, are you?

371
00:46:32.792 --> 00:46:34.251
Do what you want.

372
00:46:36.420 --> 00:46:38.339
GYRO CAPTAIN:
We're partners.

373
00:46:46.639 --> 00:46:49.934
You and me, we're partners.

374
00:46:50.643 --> 00:46:52.103
Partners!

375
00:47:49.910 --> 00:47:52.329
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

376
00:47:57.585 --> 00:47:59.670
[SCREAMS]

377
00:48:00.504 --> 00:48:01.672
Go. Go.

378
00:48:03.841 --> 00:48:05.843
[SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

379
00:48:27.656 --> 00:48:28.866
[MAN SCREAMS]

380
00:50:03.502 --> 00:50:04.837
[WOMAN GASPS]

381
00:50:08.549 --> 00:50:10.885
[HORN BLARING]

382
00:50:50.174 --> 00:50:51.508
- Whoo!
- Aah!

383
00:50:58.682 --> 00:51:00.517
[MAN YELLING]

384
00:51:32.466 --> 00:51:35.094
HUMUNGUS:
My dogs, run. The gate.

385
00:51:39.807 --> 00:51:44.103
The gate. The gate. The gate.

386
00:51:51.235 --> 00:51:52.695
[SCREAMING]

387
00:52:59.303 --> 00:53:00.554
[MAN SCREAMING]

388
00:53:04.141 --> 00:53:07.603
You. You can run, but you can't hide.

389
00:53:33.837 --> 00:53:35.839
CURMUDGEON:
You did a great job.

390
00:53:36.382 --> 00:53:37.883
That's my man.

391
00:53:38.634 --> 00:53:40.177
That's my man.

392
00:53:40.344 --> 00:53:42.304
Don't go overboard now.

393
00:53:43.472 --> 00:53:46.642
No, don't touch, please.
It's a precision instrument.

394
00:53:49.436 --> 00:53:51.230
Don't touch.

395
00:53:51.855 --> 00:53:53.690
Ah, ah, ah.

396
00:53:58.737 --> 00:54:00.197
Don't touch.

397
00:54:00.489 --> 00:54:02.533
Shoo, shoo. Go.

398
00:54:02.825 --> 00:54:03.992
[GROWLING]

399
00:54:04.368 --> 00:54:05.869
Shoo! Shoo!

400
00:54:06.036 --> 00:54:07.121
Go on.

401
00:54:10.457 --> 00:54:13.210
Tell me, son, this machine of yours…

402
00:54:14.545 --> 00:54:16.672
… it can take two, can it?

403
00:54:18.674 --> 00:54:19.925
Possibly.

404
00:54:25.222 --> 00:54:26.348
ZETTA:
All right?

405
00:54:26.515 --> 00:54:29.977
I'm okay. Just get them organized,
we're moving out tonight.

406
00:54:34.148 --> 00:54:37.401
ZETTA: Okay, listen, everyone.
We're going out tonight.

407
00:54:37.568 --> 00:54:39.945
You all know what to do,
just get on with it.

408
00:54:40.112 --> 00:54:42.739
Timbo, Derek, Pappagallo's been hurt.

409
00:54:44.241 --> 00:54:45.742
How's the rig?

410
00:54:46.910 --> 00:54:48.579
ZETTA:
The rig. How is she?

411
00:54:48.745 --> 00:54:50.080
A cracked timing case cover.

412
00:54:50.247 --> 00:54:52.249
It's broken some teeth
off the timing gears.

413
00:54:52.416 --> 00:54:54.126
It's got a cracked timing case cover.

414
00:54:54.293 --> 00:54:56.795
It's broken a couple of teeth
off the timing gears.

415
00:54:56.962 --> 00:55:00.340
- The radiator's damaged at the core.
- The radiator's damaged at the core.

416
00:55:00.507 --> 00:55:03.093
- A cracked water pump.
- It's got a cracked water pump.

417
00:55:03.260 --> 00:55:06.638
- And a fractured injector line.
- And it's got a fractured injector line.

418
00:55:06.805 --> 00:55:08.015
Well, what does all that mean?

419
00:55:08.182 --> 00:55:10.517
ZETTA:
Yeah, okay, but what does that mean?

420
00:55:11.059 --> 00:55:12.936
- What does that mean?
- Twenty-four hours.

421
00:55:13.103 --> 00:55:14.605
Twenty-four hours.

422
00:55:15.939 --> 00:55:17.316
They've got 12.

423
00:55:18.192 --> 00:55:19.943
ZETTA: You've got 12.
- Okay.

424
00:55:20.110 --> 00:55:21.111
Okay.

425
00:55:21.278 --> 00:55:23.655
ZETTA:
Let's get him down. Quick, come on.

426
00:55:29.077 --> 00:55:31.622
Listen, I was wrong about you…

427
00:55:32.039 --> 00:55:33.582
… and I'm sorry.

428
00:55:41.381 --> 00:55:43.383
[ALL CHATTERING]

429
00:55:49.306 --> 00:55:50.432
MAX:
Heel.

430
00:55:50.599 --> 00:55:53.477
CURMUDGEON: It's been a long time
since I've seen driving like that, man.

431
00:55:53.644 --> 00:55:55.562
You're okay by me, son.

432
00:55:55.729 --> 00:55:59.399
With you driving that rig, we got it licked!
Nice to have you aboard, son.

433
00:55:59.566 --> 00:56:02.361
I've been saving those.
I want you to have them.

434
00:56:06.323 --> 00:56:08.200
Thank you, and welcome.

435
00:56:11.370 --> 00:56:14.289
It's been a pleasure doing business
with you, but I'm leaving.

436
00:56:14.456 --> 00:56:16.333
I'm leaving. Thanks.

437
00:56:23.340 --> 00:56:24.967
LOOKOUT:
Oh, my God, look!

438
00:56:25.133 --> 00:56:26.677
Up on the hill!

439
00:56:27.344 --> 00:56:30.097
They're stringing them up, the bastards!

440
00:56:31.974 --> 00:56:33.058
Look!

441
00:56:39.356 --> 00:56:41.483
HUMUNGUS:
You have defied me.

442
00:56:42.317 --> 00:56:46.697
You will know the vengeance
of Lord Humungus.

443
00:56:47.823 --> 00:56:49.408
I promise you…

444
00:56:50.367 --> 00:56:51.868
… nobody…

445
00:56:52.452 --> 00:56:56.206
… nobody gets out of here alive.

446
00:57:05.716 --> 00:57:08.218
[HUMUNGUS SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

447
00:57:38.373 --> 00:57:40.292
[WIND HOWLING]

448
00:57:47.299 --> 00:57:51.678
ZETTA: Who's supposed to be helping out
with the drums? Come on!

449
00:57:53.013 --> 00:57:55.932
Hey, don't forget,
don't waste a bit before we leave.

450
00:57:59.102 --> 00:58:00.646
Just wanna catch the pigs.

451
00:58:00.812 --> 00:58:03.106
Come on with the drums, come on!

452
00:58:03.273 --> 00:58:05.400
Is anybody helping over there?

453
00:58:05.692 --> 00:58:07.694
[SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

454
00:58:09.237 --> 00:58:10.447
Hey, come on!

455
00:58:43.647 --> 00:58:46.733
What's wrong? Come on.

456
00:58:47.234 --> 00:58:50.696
It just seems really wrong,
sneaking away like this.

457
00:58:50.862 --> 00:58:52.322
What?

458
00:58:54.700 --> 00:58:57.869
But you said you wanted to come,
sweetheart.

459
00:58:58.078 --> 00:58:59.830
I know I did, but…

460
00:59:00.997 --> 00:59:04.292
Look, you're scared. Now, come on,
it'll be much safer up there.

461
00:59:04.459 --> 00:59:06.795
- What are we waiting for, eh?
- No, don't.

462
00:59:08.797 --> 00:59:10.507
This is my family.

463
00:59:12.008 --> 00:59:14.469
I'm not gonna leave these people.

464
00:59:15.721 --> 00:59:17.139
I'm staying.

465
00:59:19.433 --> 00:59:20.809
I'm sorry.

466
00:59:30.652 --> 00:59:33.739
WARRIOR WOMAN:
Come on, keep it together.

467
00:59:50.964 --> 00:59:53.550
CURMUDGEON: I told you, he's leaving.
What did I tell you?

468
00:59:53.717 --> 00:59:55.218
Look, he's leaving.

469
00:59:57.053 --> 01:00:01.433
Look, I don't have time for long speeches.
I want you to drive the tanker.

470
01:00:03.226 --> 01:00:04.394
Sorry.

471
01:00:05.896 --> 01:00:09.107
We had a contract.
I kept my part of the bargain.

472
01:00:10.150 --> 01:00:12.194
We'll make a new contract.

473
01:00:15.947 --> 01:00:17.949
I've got all I need here.

474
01:00:18.200 --> 01:00:22.370
You don't have a future.
I could offer you that. Rebuild our lives.

475
01:00:22.579 --> 01:00:23.622
Max…

476
01:00:23.872 --> 01:00:25.957
… buy a ticket for 2000 miles.

477
01:00:26.124 --> 01:00:30.420
You have to come, sonny.
This is where we're going. Paradise.

478
01:00:31.254 --> 01:00:33.089
Two thousand miles from here.

479
01:00:33.423 --> 01:00:35.842
Fresh water, plenty of sunshine.

480
01:00:36.384 --> 01:00:38.386
Nothing to do but breed.

481
01:00:40.096 --> 01:00:41.431
No, thanks.

482
01:00:42.182 --> 01:00:45.185
What is it with you, huh?
What are you looking for?

483
01:00:45.852 --> 01:00:48.688
Come on, Max,
everyone's looking for something.

484
01:00:49.272 --> 01:00:51.233
You happy out there, are you?

485
01:00:51.399 --> 01:00:54.486
Eh? Wandering?
One day blurring into another?

486
01:00:55.403 --> 01:00:58.281
You're a scavenger, Max.
You're a maggot.

487
01:00:58.949 --> 01:01:00.200
Do you know that?

488
01:01:00.367 --> 01:01:03.119
You're living off the corpse
of the old world.

489
01:01:03.620 --> 01:01:05.831
Tell me your story.
Come on, tell me your story.

490
01:01:05.997 --> 01:01:07.499
What burned you out?

491
01:01:07.666 --> 01:01:09.167
Kill one man too many?

492
01:01:09.334 --> 01:01:11.670
See too many people die?
Lose some family?

493
01:01:11.837 --> 01:01:16.132
Oh, so that's it. You lost some family.
That make you something special, does it?

494
01:01:16.716 --> 01:01:17.968
Listen to me.

495
01:01:40.365 --> 01:01:43.159
Do you think
you're the only one that's suffered?

496
01:01:43.577 --> 01:01:47.289
We've all been through it in here.
But we haven't given up.

497
01:01:48.623 --> 01:01:51.334
We're still human beings with dignity.

498
01:01:51.960 --> 01:01:55.589
But you, you're out there
with the garbage.

499
01:01:56.131 --> 01:01:57.674
You're nothing.

500
01:02:25.076 --> 01:02:28.121
["HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU" CHIMES]

501
01:02:39.341 --> 01:02:40.800
Get out, kid.

502
01:02:43.720 --> 01:02:45.722
Come on, get out of here.

503
01:03:07.035 --> 01:03:09.663
Go on, get out. Scat. Get out.

504
01:03:41.236 --> 01:03:43.113
You're letting him go?

505
01:03:44.948 --> 01:03:47.283
Well, let's keep his vehicle, at least.

506
01:03:48.076 --> 01:03:51.746
He fulfilled his contract.
He's an honorable man.

507
01:03:53.289 --> 01:03:55.959
Okay, so who's gonna drive the tanker?

508
01:03:57.293 --> 01:03:58.378
I am.

509
01:04:25.238 --> 01:04:27.699
They've got you wrong,
you're not a coward.

510
01:04:27.866 --> 01:04:30.326
Stupid maybe, but not a coward.

511
01:04:31.494 --> 01:04:33.830
You're making a serious mistake…

512
01:04:34.956 --> 01:04:37.042
… splitting a great team.

513
01:04:37.959 --> 01:04:40.712
You and me together,
think of the possibilities.

514
01:04:40.879 --> 01:04:43.840
See you around, maybe.
Goodbye, good luck.

515
01:05:05.320 --> 01:05:07.447
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

516
01:05:11.409 --> 01:05:12.410
WEZ:
We go!

517
01:05:23.505 --> 01:05:26.216
HUMUNGUS:
You disobey me. You puppy.

518
01:06:16.891 --> 01:06:18.893
[WIND HOWLING]

519
01:06:28.945 --> 01:06:31.281
Toadie, the gas. Hurry up.

520
01:06:39.622 --> 01:06:42.458
Don't waste him. If he's alive…

521
01:06:43.459 --> 01:06:44.794
… I want him.

522
01:07:10.987 --> 01:07:15.325
TOADIE: The tanks are full, O mighty Wez,
and it's all yours!

523
01:07:25.043 --> 01:07:26.502
[DOG GROWLING]

524
01:07:26.669 --> 01:07:28.004
[DOG YELPS]

525
01:08:10.380 --> 01:08:11.881
WEZ:
It's all over.

526
01:08:12.799 --> 01:08:14.092
Let's go.

527
01:08:26.437 --> 01:08:28.898
LOOKOUT:
Look, out there. Northwest.

528
01:08:37.073 --> 01:08:38.574
GYRO CAPTAIN:
Oh, hell.

529
01:08:41.077 --> 01:08:42.912
You blew it, you fool.

530
01:09:52.815 --> 01:09:55.234
[PEOPLE SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

531
01:10:00.198 --> 01:10:02.742
Relax, partner.

532
01:10:04.952 --> 01:10:07.288
[LAUGHING]

533
01:10:39.946 --> 01:10:41.364
[THUMP]

534
01:10:43.491 --> 01:10:45.493
[FOOTSTEPS]

535
01:10:50.373 --> 01:10:52.208
[PEOPLE SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY NEARBY]

536
01:11:00.174 --> 01:11:01.759
[COUGHS]

537
01:11:39.130 --> 01:11:41.007
PAPPAGALLO:
I'll be driving the tanker.

538
01:11:42.133 --> 01:11:45.136
We're gonna crash or crash through.

539
01:11:46.804 --> 01:11:50.141
Now, at this point, that's all they want.
The tanker.

540
01:11:50.766 --> 01:11:52.894
So they'll come straight after us.

541
01:11:53.060 --> 01:11:55.771
So we'll use that to punch our way out…

542
01:11:56.063 --> 01:11:58.941
… which will give all of you
a very, very good chance.

543
01:11:59.442 --> 01:12:00.943
Now, don't hesitate.

544
01:12:01.110 --> 01:12:05.198
Once you're outside there,
split up and go as hard as you can.

545
01:12:06.574 --> 01:12:08.534
Now, 200 miles to the north…

546
01:12:09.243 --> 01:12:13.623
… there's a place with a bridge
called Powder River.

547
01:12:14.040 --> 01:12:15.958
That's our rendezvous.

548
01:12:17.293 --> 01:12:19.086
Give us till sunset.

549
01:12:20.129 --> 01:12:23.716
If we haven't made it by then,
keep going.

550
01:12:24.592 --> 01:12:26.761
Good enough for me to build,
but not to ride on?

551
01:12:26.928 --> 01:12:29.514
- You are not coming on this tanker!
- I sweated blood on this…

552
01:12:29.680 --> 01:12:32.391
… and no bastard's gonna tell me
to ride in no school bus!

553
01:12:32.558 --> 01:12:34.143
ZETTA:
Okay, settle down!

554
01:12:34.519 --> 01:12:36.646
If it's all the same to you…

555
01:12:38.314 --> 01:12:40.233
… I'll drive that tanker.

556
01:12:41.400 --> 01:12:45.154
The offer is closed. Too late for deals.

557
01:12:45.863 --> 01:12:48.366
No deals. I wanna drive that truck.

558
01:12:49.492 --> 01:12:52.328
Why? Why the big change of heart?

559
01:12:52.495 --> 01:12:54.330
Believe me, I haven't got a choice.

560
01:12:54.497 --> 01:12:56.624
And how do you think you'll do it?

561
01:12:56.791 --> 01:13:00.169
I mean, look at you.
You couldn't even drive a wheelchair.

562
01:13:01.671 --> 01:13:04.757
You should look at yourself, Max.
You're a mess.

563
01:13:06.175 --> 01:13:08.052
Come on, cut the crap.

564
01:13:09.845 --> 01:13:12.181
I'm the best chance you've got.

565
01:13:20.523 --> 01:13:22.316
PAPPAGALLO:
Right, let's get moving.

566
01:13:34.203 --> 01:13:36.205
[ALL CHATTERING]

567
01:14:23.586 --> 01:14:25.713
[ENGINE STARTS]

568
01:14:34.096 --> 01:14:36.307
Move that kid! Get rid of him!

569
01:14:41.020 --> 01:14:42.772
[GROWLING]

570
01:15:34.031 --> 01:15:36.033
[TRUCK HORN BLARING]

571
01:15:40.705 --> 01:15:42.707
[MEN SHOUTING]

572
01:15:52.675 --> 01:15:53.968
GYRO CAPTAIN:
Oh, shit!

573
01:18:27.079 --> 01:18:28.706
[WEZ LAUGHS]

574
01:18:42.887 --> 01:18:44.263
[CHEERS]

575
01:19:05.284 --> 01:19:06.577
[WEZ LAUGHS]

576
01:19:09.204 --> 01:19:13.292
Go! Go, go, go, go!

577
01:19:25.346 --> 01:19:27.139
[ZETTA SCREAMING]

578
01:20:18.649 --> 01:20:20.442
[YELLS]

579
01:20:23.737 --> 01:20:25.739
I'm all right, I'm all right.

580
01:20:28.575 --> 01:20:29.785
[GRUNTS]

581
01:20:29.952 --> 01:20:31.745
[WEZ LAUGHS]

582
01:20:31.954 --> 01:20:33.789
WEZ:
Move it. Move it.

583
01:21:05.571 --> 01:21:07.990
Come on, come on, come on!

584
01:21:43.859 --> 01:21:45.277
Whoa!

585
01:21:56.622 --> 01:21:58.457
[LAUGHS]

586
01:22:08.842 --> 01:22:11.345
[SCREAMING]

587
01:23:03.897 --> 01:23:06.942
MAN:
The tire! Shoot the tire!

588
01:24:41.328 --> 01:24:43.497
[LAUGHING]

589
01:24:46.166 --> 01:24:48.460
[WEZ YELLING]

590
01:25:03.558 --> 01:25:05.060
[WEZ SCREAMS]

591
01:25:07.187 --> 01:25:08.939
[MAX GRUNTING]

592
01:25:09.815 --> 01:25:11.191
[CHUCKLING]

593
01:25:11.358 --> 01:25:13.277
[FERAL KID GRUNTING]

594
01:25:41.221 --> 01:25:43.682
PAPPAGALLO:
Boy! Come on, jump!

595
01:25:44.725 --> 01:25:45.976
Come on, jump!

596
01:25:46.727 --> 01:25:47.728
I say.

597
01:25:48.603 --> 01:25:49.938
We've won.

598
01:25:50.480 --> 01:25:52.232
It's over, boy.

599
01:26:40.781 --> 01:26:42.866
[YELLING]

600
01:27:40.549 --> 01:27:41.675
MAX:
Hey, kid.

601
01:27:42.592 --> 01:27:44.302
Get the bullet. The bullet.

602
01:27:44.719 --> 01:27:46.513
Get up. Go on.

603
01:27:50.684 --> 01:27:52.185
Get the shell.

604
01:27:53.854 --> 01:27:55.230
Get the shell.

605
01:27:55.397 --> 01:27:57.149
Come on. Come on, go!

606
01:28:26.094 --> 01:28:28.096
[BOTH SCREAMING]

607
01:29:39.376 --> 01:29:41.378
[WIND HOWLING]

608
01:30:56.786 --> 01:30:58.913
[ENGINE CLATTERING]

609
01:31:29.110 --> 01:31:32.447
NARRATOR: <i>And so began
the journey north to safety</i>…

610
01:31:33.114 --> 01:31:34.783
…<i>to our place in the sun.</i>

611
01:31:35.367 --> 01:31:39.371
<i>Among us we found a new leader,
the man who came from the sky</i>…

612
01:31:39.829 --> 01:31:41.498
…<i>the Gyro Captain.</i>

613
01:31:41.998 --> 01:31:44.292
<i>And just as Pappagallo had planned</i>…

614
01:31:44.459 --> 01:31:47.796
…<i>we traveled far beyond
the reach of men on machines.</i>

615
01:31:48.672 --> 01:31:52.634
<i>The juice, the precious juice,
was hidden in the vehicles.</i>

616
01:31:54.386 --> 01:31:56.596
<i>As for me, I grew to manhood</i>…

617
01:31:57.263 --> 01:32:00.183
…<i>in the fullness of time,
I became the leader</i>…

618
01:32:00.350 --> 01:32:02.977
…<i>the chief of the Great Northern Tribe.</i>

619
01:32:04.896 --> 01:32:06.731
<i>And the Road Warrior?</i>

620
01:32:07.607 --> 01:32:10.235
<i>That was the last we ever saw of him.</i>

621
01:32:11.152 --> 01:32:15.323
<i>He lives now only in my memories.</i>

